Raunchy details emerge in court, painting a rather disturbing picture of the final hours of Zulu Prince Lethukuthula. He was found dead at his home last month. eNCAs Khayelihle Khumalo filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Raunchy details emerged in court, painting a rather disturbing picture of the final hours of Prince Lethukuthula Zulu. He was found dead at his home last month. The five suspects, four women, and one man allegedly connected to his death appeared before the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Thursday. READ: Prince Lethukuthula Zulu murder case postponed The four women admitted in court to being sex workers and said they had met the prince in one of the popular bars in Randburg. One of the accused also claimed that the late Zulu prince might have taken drugs on the night he died. The suspects have asked to be released, as they say, they don't pose a flight risk. The matter has been postponed to next week. For more details on this story, watch the video above.